    <div class="book-container">
        <!-- Title Page -->
        <div class="page title-page">
            <div class="hammer-nail-icon">üî®üìç</div>
            <h1 class="main-title">The Hammer & The Nail</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">A Parable About Pain, Purpose, and Precision</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 1 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">1</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                In the quiet stillness of a forgotten workshop, a small silver nail lay alone on a wooden table. He stared at the ceiling, wondering aloud:
                <div class="dialogue">"Why am I even here? Day after day, I do nothing. I just... lie here."</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 2 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">2</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                Across the table, a heavy hammer rested in silence. His head was worn but proud.
                <br><br>
                The nail turned and asked, <span class="dialogue">"Do you know what I'm for? Why I was made?"</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 3 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">3</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                The hammer looked at him with wise, steady eyes.
                <div class="dialogue">"You'll find out soon enough," he said. "But you must be ready."</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 4 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">4</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                Suddenly, a large human hand reached into the workshop.
                <br><br>
                The nail was plucked from the table and placed against a wooden beam. The hammer was raised into the air.
                <div class="dialogue">"Wait... what is happening?!"</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 5 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">5</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                <div class="sound-effect">THUD!</div>
                The hammer struck the nail's head. The impact echoed.
                <div class="dialogue">"Ouch! That hurts!"</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 6 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">6</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                <div class="dialogue">"I'm not striking you to hurt you," said the hammer. "I'm striking you to help you."</div>
                <div class="dialogue">"Help me?! This feels like pain!"</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 7 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">7</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                <div class="dialogue">"Sometimes pain is part of purpose," the hammer replied. "You were never meant to stay on the surface."</div>
                <div class="dialogue">"But I'm being driven down... I'm sinking."</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 8 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">8</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                <div class="dialogue">"Yes," said the hammer. "Because only by going deep can you hold things together."</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 9 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">9</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                Strike after strike, the nail felt pressure, heat, and fear. He wanted to scream. He wanted to escape.
                <div class="dialogue">"This is too much," he whispered.</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 10 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">10</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                <div class="dialogue">"I know," said the hammer gently. "But something beautiful is being built ‚Äî and you are a part of it."</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 11 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">11</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                The hammer finally stopped. Silence returned to the room.
                <br><br>
                The nail was now embedded deep, holding two beams together ‚Äî strong, invisible, necessary.
                <div class="dialogue">"Did I do that?" he asked.</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 12 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">12</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                <div class="dialogue">"Yes," said the hammer. "You are what keeps it all from falling apart. Without you, none of this holds."</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 13 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">13</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                The hand lifted the finished piece: a small, bright birdhouse.
                <br><br>
                From a distance, it looked simple. But the nail knew what it took to hold it all together.
                <br><br>
                A bird landed inside and chirped. üê¶
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 14 -->
        <div class="page">
            <div class="page-number">14</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                The nail smiled quietly from within the wood.
                <br><br>
                He no longer feared the strikes.
                <br><br>
                He understood them.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 15 - Reflection -->
        <div class="page reflection-page">
            <div class="page-number">15</div>
            <h2 style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 30px; font-size: 2em;">Reflection</h2>
            <div class="page-content">
                Most people stay on the surface.
                <br><br>
                They avoid discomfort. They fear going deep. They chase safety, pleasure, popularity. But in doing so, they miss their purpose.
                <br><br>
                They live loud but empty lives. Busy but disconnected. Seen, but not grounded.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 16 -->
        <div class="page reflection-page">
            <div class="page-number">16</div>
            <div class="page-content">
                But those who are willing to endure a few well-placed strikes ‚Äî those who choose depth over noise ‚Äî are the ones who hold things together.
                <br><br>
                Your pressure might not be punishment. It might be precision.
                <br><br>
                <strong>You're not being buried. You're being planted.</strong>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Page 17 - Interactive Questions -->
        <div class="page reflection-page">
            <div class="page-number">17</div>
            <div class="questions">
                <h3>Interactive Reflection</h3>
                <p style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 30px; opacity: 0.9;">Click each question to explore deeper and journal your thoughts</p>
                
                <div class="interactive-prompt" onclick="togglePrompt(this)">
                    <div class="prompt-header">
                        <span>üî® What is your hammer?</span>
                        <span class="expand-icon">‚åÑ</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="prompt-content">
                        <p>Think about the challenges, pressures, or difficulties in your life right now. These might be:</p>
                        <ul style="margin: 15px 0; padding-left: 20px;">
                            <li>A demanding job or difficult boss</li>
                            <li>Financial pressure or uncertainty</li>
                            <li>Relationship conflicts or family dynamics</li>
                            <li>Health challenges or limitations</li>
                            <li>Personal failures or setbacks</li>
                            <li>Criticism from others</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Your "hammer" isn't your enemy ‚Äî it might be the tool shaping you into who you're meant to become.</strong></p>
                        <textarea class="journal-area" placeholder="Write about your current 'hammer' ‚Äî what pressure or challenge is striking you repeatedly right now?"></textarea>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="interactive-prompt" onclick="togglePrompt(this)">
                    <div class="prompt-header">
                        <span>üí™ What pressure is shaping you?</span>
                        <span class="expand-icon">‚åÑ</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="prompt-content">
                        <p>Consider how this pressure is actually changing you:</p>
                        <ul style="margin: 15px 0; padding-left: 20px;">
                            <li>What new strengths are you developing?</li>
                            <li>What skills are you being forced to learn?</li>
                            <li>How is your character being refined?</li>
                            <li>What assumptions are being challenged?</li>
                            <li>What's being stripped away that wasn't serving you?</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Like the nail being driven deeper, you might be gaining strength and stability you never knew you needed.</strong></p>
                        <textarea class="journal-area" placeholder="Describe how the pressure in your life is actually shaping you into something stronger or more purposeful..."></textarea>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="interactive-prompt" onclick="togglePrompt(this)">
                    <div class="prompt-header">
                        <span>üí° What truth is trying to drive you deeper?</span>
                        <span class="expand-icon">‚åÑ</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="prompt-content">
                        <p>Sometimes our struggles are trying to teach us something important:</p>
                        <ul style="margin: 15px 0; padding-left: 20px;">
                            <li>That surface-level success isn't fulfilling</li>
                            <li>That we're capable of more than we thought</li>
                            <li>That our real purpose involves serving others</li>
                            <li>That authenticity matters more than popularity</li>
                            <li>That depth creates more value than breadth</li>
                            <li>That we're meant to be foundational, not decorative</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>What if you're not being buried, but planted? What might grow from this season of pressure?</strong></p>
                        <textarea class="journal-area" placeholder="What deeper truth or purpose might this difficult season be preparing you for?"></textarea>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 40px; padding: 20px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 10px;">
                    <p><strong>Remember: Your life might be the foundation someone else is depending on.</strong></p>
                    <p style="margin-top: 15px; opacity: 0.9;">The nail couldn't see the birdhouse being built, but it was essential to its completion.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

