            <!-- Personal Reflection Tab -->
            <div id="personal" class="tab-content active">
                <div class="discussion-section">
                    <h3>Personal Reflection Journey</h3>
                    <div class="facilitator-note">
                        <strong>üí° Facilitator Note:</strong> These questions are designed for deep personal introspection. Take your time with each one.
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-question">
                        <strong>Opening Reflection:</strong> When have you felt most "useful" or purposeful in your life? What were the circumstances?
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-question">
                        <strong>Identifying Your Hammer:</strong> What recurring challenges or pressures do you face? Instead of seeing them as obstacles, how might they be shaping tools?
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-question">
                        <strong>Going Deeper:</strong> The nail feared "sinking" but was actually being positioned for purpose. What current situation feels like failure but might be preparation?
                    </div>

                    <div class="activity-box">
                        <strong>üìù Journaling Exercise:</strong> Write a letter from your "future self" (5 years from now) explaining how today's struggles were necessary for tomorrow's strength.
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-question">
                        <strong>Finding Your Foundation:</strong> Where in your life are you called to be "foundational" rather than visible? How can you embrace supporting roles?
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Small Group Tab -->
            <div id="small-group" class="tab-content">
                <div class="discussion-section">
                    <h3>Small Group Discussion (4-8 people)</h3>
                    <div class="facilitator-note">
                        <strong>üí° Facilitator Note:</strong> Allow 60-90 minutes. Create a safe space for vulnerability. Have tissues available.
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-format">
                        <div class="format-title">Opening (10 minutes)</div>
                        <p>Have each person share: "Describe a time when something painful turned out to be beneficial later."</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-format">
                        <div class="format-title">Story Discussion (25 minutes)</div>
                        <div class="discussion-question">
                            <strong>Q1:</strong> What part of the nail's journey resonated most with you? Why?
                        </div>
                        <div class="discussion-question">
                            <strong>Q2:</strong> The hammer says "Sometimes pain is part of purpose." Do you agree? What are the dangers of this mindset?
                        </div>
                        <div class="discussion-question">
                            <strong>Q3:</strong> How do we distinguish between purposeful pressure and destructive abuse?
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-format">
                        <div class="format-title">Personal Sharing (30 minutes)</div>
                        <div class="discussion-question">
                            <strong>Round 1:</strong> Share about a current "hammer" in your life (if comfortable)
                        </div>
                        <div class="discussion-question">
                            <strong>Round 2:</strong> Where do you need to go "deeper" instead of staying on the surface?
                        </div>
                        <div class="facilitator-note">
                            <strong>Ground Rules:</strong> No fixing or advice-giving. Listen to understand, not to respond.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="activity-box">
                        <strong>ü§ù Partner Exercise:</strong> Pair up and help each other identify one way their current struggles might be preparing them for future purpose.
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-format">
                        <div class="format-title">Closing (15 minutes)</div>
                        <p>End with each person sharing one word that describes how they want to approach challenges differently.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Workplace Tab -->
            <div id="workplace" class="tab-content">
                <div class="discussion-section">
                    <h3>Workplace & Team Development</h3>
                    <div class="facilitator-note">
                        <strong>üí° Facilitator Note:</strong> Adapt language for your company culture. Focus on professional growth and team dynamics.
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-format">
                        <div class="format-title">Team Meeting Discussion (45 minutes)</div>
                        <div class="discussion-question">
                            <strong>Opening Question:</strong> "Think of a challenging project that ultimately made you stronger. What was it?"
                        </div>
                        <div class="discussion-question">
                            <strong>Team Dynamics:</strong> How can we reframe obstacles as "hammers" that strengthen our team rather than problems that weaken us?
                        </div>
                        <div class="discussion-question">
                            <strong>Foundation Roles:</strong> The nail became invisible but essential. How do we value and recognize "foundational" team members who aren't in the spotlight?
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="activity-box">
                        <strong>üèóÔ∏è Team Exercise:</strong> "Building the Birdhouse" - Map out a recent successful project and identify who played "nail" roles (foundational but less visible) vs. "hammer" roles (applying pressure/direction).
                    </div>

                    <div class="discussion-format">
                        <div class="format-title">Leadership Development</div>
                        <div class="discussion-question">
